1. Open power shell
2. Install scoop by following commands
Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser ----------llows PowerShell to run scripts downloaded from the internet (only those signed or created locally).
Necessary for installing Scoop.

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri https://get.scoop.sh | Invoke-Expression

3. Install hookdeck using scoop

scoop bucket add hookdeck https://github.com/hookdeck/scoop-hookdeck-cli.git

scoop install hookdeck
Hookdeck lets you capture and forward webhook events locally â€” useful for testing GitHub webhooks.
Installs the Hookdeck CLI tool so you can run commands like hookdeck listen.

4. Use hookdeck listen to get payload URL
hookdeck listen 8080
Starts a local Hookdeck listener on port 8080.

Hookdeck generates a temporary public URL that forwards requests to your local server.
5. Copy URL into payload URL of webhook on GitHub repository
